"For each monitoring context, one kernel thread for the monitoring, namely "
"kdamond, is created.  The pid of kdamond can be retrieved using "
"damon_kdamond_pid()."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../mm/damon/api:14: ../include/linux/damon.h:776
msgid ""
"Once started, kdamond runs until explicitly required to be terminated or "
"every monitoring target is invalid.  The validity of the targets is checked "
"via the :c:type:`damon_operations.target_valid <damon_operations>` of "
"**ops**.  The termination can also be explicitly requested by calling "
"damon_stop().  To know if a kdamond is running, damon_is_running() can be "
"used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../mm/damon/api:14: ../include/linux/damon.h:782
